node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jake Woodard on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'HOLDING THE MASCULINE FRAME HOLDING THE FEMININE FRAME @_JAKEWOODARD Practice being grounded Pull your shoulders back Move with awareness confidence Make clear decisions Speak with intention Don't be impulsive, be conscious Soften into your body Move with flow + sensuality Connect with your heart Honor your intuition Be expressive playful Don't shrink, fill space with your radiance'.

node.text:
🔥 𝐌𝐚𝐬𝐜𝐮𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞 + 𝐅𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐅𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐞𝐬

Before I go into this, let me say that ALL humans have both masculine + feminine energies.

It’s important to know that you will use both of your energies, but you will likely identify more with one being your “core” energy.

Below are some examples of a woman holding the feminine frame and a man holding the masculine frame. You could swap these out with a man holding the feminine and a woman holding the masculine.

𝐇𝐨𝐥𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐟𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐟𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐞 𝐚𝐬 𝐚 𝐰𝐨𝐦𝐚𝐧.

Her energy is soft and gentle, and her wisdom is deep.

She’s not guarded because of past pain. She’s done the inner work to alchemize the darkness into light.

She listens carefully to the vibrations of her heart and intuition.

The noise of her mind does not cloud her because she’s integrated with her BODY + SPIRIT.

𝐇𝐨𝐥𝐝𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐦𝐚𝐬𝐜𝐮𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐟𝐫𝐚𝐦𝐞 𝐚𝐬 𝐚 𝐦𝐚𝐧.

He is balanced because he is integrated with his mind and heart.

He stands firmly rooted in consciousness.

He is clear with the direction of his life and mission.

When problems arise, he doesn’t flip out. Instead, he sits with himself. He reflects deeply upon how he wants to move forward before making a decision.

Drop a “❤️” and TAG 3 people who need to see this!

Tell me, how do you practice holding the feminine or masculine frame?

Much love,
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jake Woodard on September 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The full surrender of the feminine requires the full trust of the masculine. -Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
🔥 (𝐋𝐨𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐒𝐞𝐱𝐮𝐚𝐥 𝐀𝐭𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧) 𝐋𝐞𝐭 𝐦𝐞 𝐠𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐚𝐧 𝐞𝐱𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐉𝐨𝐡𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐀𝐬𝐡𝐥𝐞𝐲.

John identifies as having a masculine core, and Ashley identifies as having a feminine core.

In the beginning of their relationship, John does a great job of holding the masculine frame, and Ashley is very rested in her feminine essence.

She says, “I’ve never felt this safe with a man before! My heart feels so open, and my body feels soft.”

As the relationship progresses, John starts to drift away from the relationship and stops holding a strong masculine frame. He becomes overly focused on his mission and loses sight of his relationship with Ashley.

At the same time, Ashley starts to step more into her masculine in life. She gets a promotion at work and starts feeling the pressure from her boss to perform at a very high level.

When they both come home at night, they stay locked into their masculine frame of mind.

They both start noticing they are losing attraction to each other.

What’s happening at an energetic level? They are losing sexual polarity because of the excess amount of masculine energy in their relationship.

Now, they can do one of two things. They can break up and walk away, or they can fix the polarity.

They choose to fix the polarity. 🙌

John focuses on holding a strong masculine frame and making time to cultivate intimacy with his flower (Ashley)

Ashley focuses on maintaining a feminine flow throughout her day and fully surrendering into the container of the relationship when she’s with John.

John loves how the radiance of Ashley’s feminine heart fills his body. He notices that he’s so much more attracted to her. He can’t keep his hands off her!

And because Ashley feels seen and supported by John, she feels very open and receptive to his masculine energy.

Have you ever experienced this?

Drop a ”❤️” and TAG 3 people who need to see this!

Much love,
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jake Woodard on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Remember. The matrix is designed to keep you distracted. Το keep you plugged into the "machine.' The unaware mind is easily manipulated and tricked. Give a person constant "entertainment," and they become a mental prisoner. Give them excessive amounts of stimulation, and they become controlled by their ego desires. Give them fear, and they stay obedient to the system. Το break free, we must have the discipline and will to go beyond what keeps our minds enslaved. -Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
(𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐦𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐚𝐠𝐞 𝐢𝐬 𝐍𝐎𝐓 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲𝐨𝐧𝐞) 𝐖𝐡𝐲 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐬𝐨 𝐦𝐚𝐧𝐲 𝐩𝐞𝐨𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐓𝐔𝐂𝐊 𝐫𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐧𝐨𝐰?👇

I believe it's because their minds are so distracted, they rarely ever allow themselves to FEEL what’s happening within.

And if we don’t feel, we are numb. If we are numb, we become robots.

Feeling + emotions are what make us human. It’s what allows us to connect with each other. It’s what allows us to connect with ourselves.

This is one of the main reasons why most intimate relationships fail.

When it gets challenging, people abandon the relationship.

“I’ll just go find another one.”

Only to find themselves right back in the same trap.

Remember. As you awaken from this illusion, you will likely feel like the sober person at a party full of drunk people.

You’ll be judged for being different.
You’ll be criticized for being a free thinker.

But you know what? People are waking up.

Together we are rising.
Human consciousness is shifting.

The few are becoming THE MANY.

Can I get a full-body YES if you’re with me?

PS- I can’t say much about it right now, but I am putting together a powerful in-person live event for early 2022. Stay tuned 😎

Much love, 
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jake Woodard on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A woman who carries a masculine shield will not allow a masculine man to step fully into her space. Her lack of trust for masculine energy causes her to guard her heart and block love from entering. Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
“𝐈 𝐰𝐚𝐧𝐭 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐞 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐟𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐛𝐮𝐭 𝐜𝐚𝐧’𝐭 𝐭𝐫𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐦𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐡𝐨𝐥𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐦𝐚𝐬𝐜𝐮𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐬𝐩𝐚𝐜𝐞! 𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐨 𝐈 𝐝𝐨?”

My response:

You can’t trust men, or you don’t allow yourself to open FULLY because of the masculine wounds you carry?

It’s not like some man is going to come along with a magic wand, tap you on the forehead, and you’re going to fall into your feminine.

Cultivating your feminine is an internal practice.

Softening your body.
Connecting with your heart.
Utilizing your full body expression.
Feeling your emotions.
And surrendering to the flow of the life force energy that moves through you.

Imagine it like going to the gym.

You practice cultivating your feminine energy the same way.

I invite you to focus on your relationship with your inner masculine and why you feel so guarded toward men, and why you feel afraid to drop into your feminine.

node.text:
🔥 LET THEM GO.

Let that person go who you keep having to explain your worth to.

Let that person go who you have to keep chasing after.

Let that person go who doesn’t value your presence.

Let that person go who doesn’t love you the way your deep heart yearns for.

Why?

Because you’re worth so much more than some half-ass relationship that doesn’t serve you.

Years ago, I went through a really challenging breakup.

It brought me to my knees and made me really take a deeper look within myself.

To look at my wounds.

I was trying to force a relationship to work with a woman who couldn’t love me.

No matter how hard I tried, it didn’t matter.

In my heart, I knew it wasn’t the right relationship.

I kept questioning it.

Eventually, I found the courage to be honest with myself and release the relationship.

I would have NEVER allowed my fiancé Melissa to come into my life if I had stayed.

It all makes sense now.

All of the trials I went through in previous relationships prepared me for the beautiful relationship I have now.

And I truly believe that it all started with ME.

I has to heal the relationship with myself, so I could attract someone with who I was in alignment with.

You are worthy of a beautiful and fulfilling relationship. Don’t settle for someone who doesn’t love you the way you desire.

Drop a “❤️” and TAG 3 people who need to see this!

Much love,
-Jake

node.text:
I have recently been undergoing some changes that I would like to share with you.

When I started to “wake up” years ago, I cut everything out of my life.

And when I say everything, I mean everything. I didn’t even have a TV in my house. I went into deep isolation. I even moved into the mountains at one point.

I went through all of these different phases of shedding and growth to get to a place of being at peace with myself.

It was extremely dark at times.
I experienced loneliness, anxiety, depression, and lost many of my old friends.

I became so focused on being “spiritual” that I lost my sense of being human. I forgot what it felt like to be playful, to laugh, and to be FREE.

Lately, I have been feeling a deep pull to embody more of my authentic self.

I’ve always loved to have a good time. To see other people happy and laughing lights me up inside.

Even back in high school, I was always the kid having the parties because my heart has always yearned for connection. To bring people together and feel a sense of freedom through our ability to relate with one another.

Even if at the time, that relating was who could drink the most alcohol, lol.

Although I have changed some of my old bad habits, my core still remains the same.

My heart is big.
I care immensely for other people.
And I like to have a damn good time.

Here is what I have learned:

👉 Being “spiritual” or “conscious” doesn’t mean you bypass your human self.

👉 You can live a conscious life and still have fun.

👉 You don't need to be sitting in a cave, burning incense and chanting “om” to be spiritual.

👉 A major key to our freedom is found within our ability to release the illusion of being a “somebody” to fit into this world and be accepted.

Can I get a YES for the real people who are on this journey with me?

Much love,
-Jake

🤔 “𝐀𝐬 𝐚 𝐦𝐚𝐧, 𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐝𝐨 𝐈 𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐟𝐞𝐦𝐢𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐭𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠?”

If you feel like your woman is testing you, then this is when you must be the clearest with your direction and decision making. 

It may sound like her saying, “well, what do you think we should do?”

Or

“I am ok with whatever you decide.”

This is where a lot of men put the pressure back on her to make a decision.

But in this moment she is testing his clarity, direction, presence, + how grounded he is.

Resistance often starts because lack of direction in the relationship.

Women will often test a man to see if his masculine energy is sturdy enough to hold her.

As a masculine man you open the feminine through your:

Presence.
Humor.
Consistency.
Clear direction.
Unwavering confidence.
Grounded, heart connection.
Doing what you say you’re going to do.

node.text:
Can I be honest with you?

I was hesitant to post this.

Why?

Because I sometimes give way too many shits about what people might think about me.

Last night, I took my badass fiancé to the county fair.

I embraced my inner hillbilly.

I went on rides.
I played fair games.
I ate fair food.

And you know what?

I had a damn good time.

Because we all have that inner child within us that wants to play.

That wants to let go and be free.

There are too many people in the world who walk around with a constipated look on their faces.

Caring too much about what others think.
Afraid to speak how they feel.
Afraid to be their authentic self.

They are working their life away for nothing in return.

That used to be me.

Not anymore.

Who else loves to do things that make them feel like a kid again?

-Jake

He will continue to be triggered by women until he cuts the cord to the pain he carries from his mother. -Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
𝐀 𝐌𝐨𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫 𝐈𝐬 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐅𝐢𝐫𝐬𝐭 𝐖𝐨𝐦𝐚𝐧 𝐓𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐀 𝐌𝐚𝐧 𝐋𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐬

She has a significant impact on how he will relate with all women.

If he carries pain from his mother, he will likely resent the women he meets in life and not fully connect with them.

Here are a few examples of what this might look like.

A woman’s emotions or feelings easily trigger him.
He’s “clingy.”
He wants women to mother him and take care of him.
He struggles to express how he feels.
He’s emotionally unavailable.
He doesn’t respect a woman’s boundaries.

I struggled with a few of these things.

I didn’t realize for a while that I was carrying mother wounds.

When I took a deeper look, I noticed that some of the toxic patterns that manifested in my life stemmed from a mother wound.

It’s not easy to look within yourself and heal your pain. It takes extreme courage.

But I can tell you from personal experience that owning your shit, and healing it, will set you free.

-Jake
